    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-12-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="80" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <head>No. 80.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morton</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-12-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 28,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Pork again prohibited until the Chamber passes upon the bill to inaugurate a
                        system of inspection. Meantime it will be admitted at the ports of Havre,
                        Bordeaux, and Nantes, subject to inspection under the direction of the
                        chambers of commerce of those cities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>MORTON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
